# SignReady PDF Privacy Policy

**Effective Date:** [Insert Date]

Thank you for using **SignReady PDF**. This Privacy Policy explains how SignReady PDF handles information when you use the app.

## Overview

SignReady PDF is designed as a local PDF utility. The app helps users prepare PDFs for signing, upload, email, correction, compression, metadata removal, and form-flattening workflows.

SignReady PDF does **not** collect, upload, sell, rent, or share your PDF documents or document contents.

## Local Processing

All PDF processing happens locally on your device.

SignReady PDF does not upload your PDFs to a server. The app does not require an account, login, subscription, cloud service, or external document-processing service.

The app may create temporary working files on your device while processing a PDF. These files are used only to complete the selected workflow and are not transmitted to the developer or any external service.

## Original Files

SignReady PDF does not overwrite your original PDF.

Each workflow creates a separate output copy. You are responsible for reviewing the output file before sending, uploading, signing, or relying on it.

## Documents and File Contents

SignReady PDF does not collect or transmit:

* PDF document contents
* PDF filenames
* PDF metadata
* Passwords
* Signatures
* Form data
* Annotations or comments
* File paths
* Exported output files

## Password-Protected PDFs

If a PDF requires a password to open, SignReady PDF may ask you to enter the document open password.

Passwords are used only locally on your device to open the selected PDF. SignReady PDF does not store, transmit, log, guess, crack, brute-force, or bypass unknown passwords.

## Network Activity

SignReady PDF does not use network-based PDF processing.

The app does not upload documents to any server and does not send document information to the developer.

## Analytics and Tracking

SignReady PDF does not use third-party analytics, advertising trackers, or tracking technologies.

The app does not track you across apps or websites.

## Personal Information

SignReady PDF does not require you to provide personal information to use the app.

The developer may receive personal information only if you choose to contact support directly, such as by sending an email. Information you provide in a support request will be used only to respond to your request.

Please do not send confidential, legal, financial, medical, personnel, customer, student, signature, workplace, or otherwise sensitive documents when requesting support. If a sample PDF is needed, please use a non-sensitive test file.

## App Store and Platform Services

If you download SignReady PDF through the Apple App Store, Apple may collect information according to Apple’s own privacy policies and App Store terms. SignReady PDF does not control Apple’s collection or processing of App Store, purchase, crash, or device-related information.

## Children’s Privacy

SignReady PDF is not intended to collect information from children. The app does not knowingly collect personal information from children.

## Important PDF and Signature Notice

Editing, rebuilding, flattening, unlocking, or compressing a signed PDF may invalidate prior digital signatures. Some workflows may rasterize pages and may not preserve selectable text, links, form fields, annotations, accessibility data, or signature validity.

SignReady PDF creates new output copies for review, correction, upload, signing, or re-signature. Review all output files carefully before using them.

## Third-Party Services and Affiliation

SignReady PDF is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by DocuSign, Adobe, Dropbox Sign, or any other electronic signature provider.

## Changes to This Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. If changes are made, the updated policy will be posted at the same location with a revised effective date.

